body:
### Description

When creating an `SKSvgCanvas` in a thread (via `Task.Run()`), `<text>` elements will sometimes have their text value and `x`/`y` attribute values removed.

The more text elements being drawn and the more threads running the same task, the more likely the problem is to occur.

This is an issue for my application because it renders many plots to SVG in parallel tasks, and this is how I found the bug. This affects all SkiaSharp 3.x versions on Windows. Linux is unaffected.

This is a regression from SkiaSharp 2.88.9 which does not have the bug.

### Code

GitHub repository with full source code to reproduce: https://github.com/jankurianski/skiasharp-svg-text-missing-bug

The salient parts of the reproduction are:
```cs
Regex containsBlankTextElement = new Regex(@">\s+</text>");
// The bug will occur even with 1 text element, but more increases the chance of hitting it.
int numTextElementsPerTask = 10;

Func<int, string> drawSvgFunc = (int taskI) => {
    using (var svgStream = new MemoryStream()) {
        using (var canvas = SKSvgCanvas.Create(new SKRect(0, 0, 500, 500), svgStream)) {
            for (int i = 0; i < numTextElementsPerTask; i++) {
                using var paint = ...
                using var typeface = ...
                using var font = ...

                var text = $"Hello, World {i + 1} of {numTextElementsPerTask}!";
                canvas.DrawText(text, 10, i * 15 + 20, align, font, paint);
            }
        }
        svgStream.Position = 0;
        svgBytes = svgStream.ToArray();
    }
    var svgStringDecoded = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(svgBytes);
    bool containsBlankText = containsBlankTextElement.IsMatch(svgStringDecoded);
    if (containsBlankText) {
        Console.WriteLine($"**bug found** during generation task {taskI} in first check");
    }
    return svgStringDecoded;
};

await Task.WhenAll(
    Enumerable.Range(0, 5)
    .Select(i => Task.Run(() => drawSvgFunc(i)))
    ).ConfigureAwait(false);
```

### Expected Behavior

`<text>` elements should always contain the text values, even if `SKSvgCanvas` is created in a thread:

```
<text font-size="14" font-family="Arial" x="10, 20.110352, 27.896484, 31.006836, 34.117188, 41.90332, 45.792969, 49.682617, 62.896484, 70.682617, 75.344727, 78.455078, 86.241211, 90.130859, 97.916992, 101.80664, 109.59277, 113.48242, 117.37207, 125.1582, 132.94434, " y="20, ">
Hello, World 1 of 10!
</text>
```

### Actual Behavior

`<text>` elements are missing their text values as well as `x` and `y` attribute values:

```
<text font-size="14" font-family="Arial" x="" y="">

</text>
```

### Version of SkiaSharp

3.116.0 (Current)
3.119.1
3.119.2-preview.1

### Last Known Good Version of SkiaSharp

2.88.9 (Previous)

### IDE / Editor

Visual Studio Code (Windows)

### Platform / Operating System

Windows

### Platform / Operating System Version

Windows 11.

